    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="550"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/96.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to Haiti</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1019.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith copy and
                    translation of a note of the Dominican Legation to the Haitian Government
                    relative to the boundary question.<note n="1" xml:id="d550fn1">Not printed; it
                        discusses discrepancies between the maps, and the consequent divergence of
                        opinion relating to the status quo line.</note> The copy was furnished me by
                    the Dominican Legation. Since its receipt I have had several informal talks on
                    the subject with Minister Henriquez and Secretary Léger. I have tried to impress
                    both parties with the necessity for prompt action looking to the speedy
                    settlement of the question rather than long discussions which accomplish
                    nothing. * * *</p>
                <p>I have [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. W. Furniss.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
